application.label: XSLT
application.name: various XSLT-Stylesheets for porcessing the XML file

normalization.p: In the reference score violoncellos and contrabasses were split into separate staves from m227 to m240. In this encoding they were left on the same staff, but were placed onto separate layers with additional labels. The reason was a technical problem to render an additional staff only in one segment of the score.

editorialDecl.p: Basset and soprano clarinet parts are encoded in separate staff and are strongly connected with each other: 1) A note in the soprano clarinet part which is same to the basset clarinet gets a @corresp attribute; 2) @xml:id of any basset clarinet element (incl. slur, dynam, etc.) gets an ending '_bc', the first part is identical, e.g. xml:id="d1e160406" (soprano) and xml:id="d1e160406_bc" (basset).
ossia (e.g. in measures 204-205) were encoded as 'choice' as well as alternative accidentals over the notes (e.g. measure 21).
Clarinet part in the tutti sections is encoded with grey color in order to help a clarinetist to find solo sections faster.

projectDesc.p: The aims was of the encoding are: 1) Merge traditional and reconstructed versions; 2) Encode differences between soprano and basset clarinet parts; 3) Encode alternatives; 4) Prepare the file for rendering in order to enable convenient usage by a clarinetist (change views, interaction and so on).

samplingDecl.p: The encoding includes the first movement.

changeDesc.p: finished encoding of the traditional version
Added @staff='5' with basset clarinet part and updated elements references of slur, tie, dynam etc.
Marked relations between soprano and basset with the aid of @corresp and xml:id's
Marked tutti in the clarinet parts with @color and @label
Encoded ossia's and alternative accidentals as choice
